content:
You can view, hide, and rename dataset columns. Users with view-only access to the dataset can view the names and API names of columns.

To configure the dataset columns, click Fields while exploring the dataset.
Hover over the right edge of a column to reveal its context menu.
Click the arrow to reveal the context menu.
Select Rename to rename the column's visible name.
You can also click any column's name to edit it. You can copy the column's API name, but you cannot change it.

To display every column's API name in the Dataset Fields list of columns, click Show Field API Names.

To hide a column, select Hide from its context menu.
The column is hidden from users who explore the dataset and from all lenses or dashboards that currently use the dataset. However, the column is still accessible via JSON, REST API, and SAQL queries.

For measures, you can choose to apply a number format.
Click Save to save the changes.
title: Configure and Customize Dataset Columns
